<P>
SAMUEL WESLEY PERRY III; PSYCHOANALYST AND AIDS RESEARCHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Samuel Wesley Perry III, 53, a psychoanalyst noted for his research on 
AIDS.Perry documented the psychological course of prolonged infection and made 
a record of adults who tested positive for HIV. His research led him to 
conclude that most patients were able to cope reasonably well over time if 
given proper counseling. He was a professor of psychiatry and associate 
chairman of research at the New York Hospital-Cornell Medical Center, where he 
had worked since 1977. He also was an analyst at Columbia University's 
Psychoanalytic Center. In Tenafly, N.J., on Tuesday of cancer. 
