<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIKE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Bravo to Mike Clary for his informative piece on Daytona Bike Week! I longed 
for the day The Times would print a truthful, balanced article about 
motorcyclists, instead of the usual media stereotyping. Clary noted that 99% of 
motorcyclists are fun-loving, upstanding citizens.That Bike Week is Daytona's 
"biggest, best-behaved" and richest event should send a message to Southern 
California governments. 
</P>
<P>
 Bike week will gross Daytona merchants $211 million in one week. That ain't 
chump change, folks! With our local economies, and particularly tourism, in the 
dumps, perhaps we should reconsider our attitudes toward motorcyclists and 
motor racing in general. After all, we have weather year-round that Daytona 
gets only in winter. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California is also home to the largest group of off-road riders in 
the nation. Every weekend, thousands of us take our families to the Mojave 
Desert to enjoy our sport in a lawful, responsible and economically stimulating 
manner. If local government leaders continue to stand by idly while the Sierra 
Club's desert closure bill sails through an uninformed Congress, they can kiss 
our money goodby. 
</P>
<P>
 DAVID W. KAY 
</P>
<P>
 Mar Vista 
</P>
