<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV WITHOUT KURALT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In these days when local TV news reporters are paid hundreds of thousands of 
dollars to cover stories that any cub police reporter could handle at one-tenth 
the pay, the announcement of Charles Kuralt's retirement is a tragedy. 
</P>
<P>
 A literate, thoughtful reporter, he endows stories with perspective, balance 
and absence of malice. He lets the story tell itself without hype, misdirected 
emphasis or distortion. And he obviously likes people. 
</P>
<P>
 There is little hope of finding others like him. If there are future Kuralts 
in the hinterlands, today's ratings-obsessed news directors will cut them off 
at the knees. 
</P>
<P>
 With Kuralt's departure, there is no reason to watch TV news. 
</P>
<P>
 PHIL WILLON 
</P>
<P>
 Palos Verdes Peninsula 
</P>
</TEXT>
