<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE BASKETBALL CHAMPIONSHIPS; ROUNDUP; PLAYA DEL REY ST. BERNARD GETS A 
SECOND TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 No matter that the Playa del Rey St. Bernard girls' basketball team lost four 
of its five starters from last season's State Division IV championship team 
because of graduation. 
</P>
<P>
 No matter because the player the Vikings had returning was Olympia Scott. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott led St. Bernard to its second consecutive title when it defeated Grass 
Valley Bear River, 53-43, Friday at the Oakland Coliseum in a rematch of last 
season's final. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott, a 6-foot-2 senior forward, and Marte Alexander, a 6-4 senior center, 
each scored 14 points to lead the Vikings (28-4). Scott also had a game-high 20 
rebounds, including nine offensive boards. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Bernard did not take control until the fourth quarter. With St. Bernard 
trailing, 43-39, Alexander and Scott combined for 10 points as the Vikings 
scored the final 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
 For St. Bernard, the game ended an era. Scott will head to Stanford next 
season and Alexander will head to Arizona. WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</TEXT>
