<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP VOLLEYBALL ROUNDUP; HUNTINGTON BEACH CONSISTENCY, MARINA ERRORS LEAD TO 
SWEEP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JANE HUANG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Capitalizing on Marina hitting errors, Huntington Beach won its second 
consecutive Sunset League match with a 15-3, 15-8, 15-0 victory Friday night at 
Marina High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Oilers (3-1, 2-0) had consistent passing and hitting from its starting 
six.Junior Jeremy Bart lead Huntington Beach with nine kills, followed by Nick 
Ziegler's eight. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our strength is that we have six guys we can set anytime," Oiler Coach Rocky 
Ciarelli said. "We pass well, and that's the key to our team." 
</P>
<P>
 In the first game, the Oilers were up, 6-2, when senior Mike Grave hit an ace 
and service winner to make it 8-2. Marina then committed four hitting errors in 
the next eight points. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings took their only lead of the match, 4-3, in the second game off two 
Mark Maculey kills. But sparked by a Steve Markham kill at 4-4, the Oilers won 
the next seven points and then won the game on another Viking error. 
</P>
<P>
 Outside hitter Mike Wirthlin led Marina with a match-high 18 kills. Maculey 
added six for the Vikings (1-5, 1-1). JANE HUANG 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031994-0105 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 024254 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
March 19, 1994, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 15; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
398 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP VOLLEYBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In another Sunset League match: 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View 3, Westminster 0 -- Jerry Johnson had a team-high eight kills for 
the Seahawks (2-2, 1-1). Westminster is 0-2 in league. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 3, Santiago 0 -- Kevin Doane had a match-high 10 kills and four 
blocks for La Quinta (3-2, 2-0). Santiago drops to 1-3, 0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Alamitos 3, Garden Grove 1 -- Jay Anderson had 17 kills, and Ben Lam 
added 14 for Rancho Alamitos, which won, 12-15, 15-13, 15-13, 15-9. Mike 
Blackner had 16 kills for host Garden Grove (1-4, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica 3, Bolsa Grande 2 -- Ian Cheesman had 19 kills, Mike Parsons added 18 
and Jake Currier had 40 assists to lead Pacifica, 15-4, 16-14, 15-17, 18-20, 
15-12. Pacifica improved to 1-4, 1-1. Mike Porter had 18 kills for Bolsa Grande 
(3-5, 0-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 3, Irvine 2 -- Though Corona del Mar (3-1, 1-1) started off 
slowly, losing its first two games, the Sea Kings turned it around with a 20-18 
victory in Game 3 and came back to win the match, 13-15, 8-15, 20-18, 15-13, 
15-5. 
</P>
<P>
 Brooks Hoppe had 30 kills and Ryan Coleman added 24 for Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine is 2-2, 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 3, University 0 -- Mitch McCoy had 18 kills to lead Newport 
Harbor, 15-8, 15-4, 15-1. Eric Vallely and Greg Slick each had nine kills and 
Wes Badorek had six kills and two blocks for the Sailors (2-2, 2-0). University 
fell to 1-1 in league. 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 3, Santa Margarita 1 -- Danny Tcheng had 13 kills and five blocks for 
host Tustin (3-1, 2-0), which won, 15-1, 16-14, 10-15, 15-6. 
</P>
