<P>
OFF THE TICKER: AND THE WINNER IS . . . (ENTER) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AMY HARMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Not a voting member of the motion picture academy? No need to feel left out. 
</P>
<P>
 ABC Television and NTN Communications Inc. will broadcast a live interactive 
version of the Academy Awards ceremony Monday night, allowing viewers to vote 
on the Oscar nominees in all major categories. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said the interactive awards show will be seen by television 
viewers throughout the United States and Canada at the 1,500 sites -- mostly 
bars and hotel lounges -- that subscribe to NTN's entertainment network. 
</P>
<P>
 Using a hand-held cordless keyboard, participants will predict the winners. 
Those correctly predicting the most winners will win prizes, among them a 
year's supply of movie passes. AMY HARMON 
