<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA BEACH; COUNCIL ENDORSES GAY-PRIDE FESTIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLIE EARNEST 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Calling it a "healthy, fine event," the City Council has voted unanimously to 
support the city's first gay and lesbian festival, a two-day celebration in 
April. 
</P>
<P>
 The council's support was sought Tuesday night by the co-chairman of Laguna 
Outreach, a gay and lesbian community group sponsoring the event. 
</P>
<P>
 Doug Reilly said the group wanted "moral support," not money, from the city in 
staging what they hope will become an annual event. 
</P>
<P>
 Reilly said the festival will benefit local businesses and generate sales 
taxes for the city. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're trying to bring people here so they will understand what we have to 
offer," he told the council. 
</P>
<P>
 "Laguna Pride Weekend," as the event is being called, will be launched April 
29, with a party at the Boom Boom Room, a local gay bar that is one of the 
festival's sponsors. 
</P>
<P>
 The festival itself will be held the next two days at the Festival of Arts 
grounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Related celebrations will be held elsewhere in town, including a "Twilight 
Block Party" at the south end of town Saturday and Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Calling it "a very fine proposal," Councilman Robert F. Gentry encouraged the 
council to support the event Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council commonly endorses local activities. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Outreach will seek support Thursday from the Chamber of Commerce.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 494-4137.LESLIE EARNEST 
</P>
</TEXT>
