<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; ANNUAL RODEO-STYLE COMPETITION TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A rodeo-style competition today and Sunday will benefit the Drug Abuse is Life 
Abuse program. 
</P>
<P>
 The 12th annual San Juan Capistrano Championship Team Penning contest starts 
at 8:30 a.m. today at the Creekside Equestrian Center, 28801 San Juan Creek 
Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunday's contest will begin at 9 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Team penning is a rodeo-style sport that gives horse riders 90 seconds to 
identify and pull out three designated head of cattle from a herd of 30 and 
then drive them into a pen. 
</P>
<P>
 The San Juan Capistrano competition is sanctioned by the World Championship 
Team Penning Assn. and draws contestants from throughout the state. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to the team penning, a Western-themed fair will be held on both 
days featuring game booths for children, food stands and raffles. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 661-1075.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
