<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA PAULA; LOCAL LEADERS INVITED TO SCHOOL SCIENCE 
FAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As in many other school districts around Ventura County, Santa Paula schools 
are having a science fair this month in preparation for the countywide science 
exhibit in April. 
</P>
<P>
 But the Santa Paula Elementary School District is putting a new twist on its 
annual science fair. 
</P>
<P>
 District officials have sent personal invitations to hundreds of local 
politicians, civic leaders and business people to attend the event, which will 
be held from 7:30 to 8:30 a.m. Wednesday at Barbara Webster School. 
</P>
<P>
 The district's science fair will feature about 2,000 projects from students in 
kindergarten through eighth grade. Sixth- through eighth-grade winners will be 
eligible to enter the Ventura County Science Fair on April 7 to 9 at the County 
Fairgrounds in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Paula Supt. David Philips said school officials see the science fair as 
an opportunity to get community leaders more involved in public schools. 
</P>
<P>
 "A large number of business leaders in our town graduated from the schools 
here, and they probably haven't seen a science fair since they went to school," 
Philips said. MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
