<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHOWERS COULD PERSIST INTO SUNDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The light showers that began Friday night may continue over Orange County, off 
and on, throughout today and possibly into Sunday, according to WeatherData, 
which provides forecasts for The Times. 
</P>
<P>
 Precipitation could reach one to two-tenths of an inch, said meteorologist 
Bruce Thoren. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's not really a major storm system," Thoren said, but winds could 
occasionally gust to 15-20 m.p.h.  
</P>
<P>
 The low-pressure system shows signs it will progressively move eastward over 
the next 12 to 24 hours, producing variable cloudiness. 
</P>
<P>
 Highs today should get into the mid 60s to low 70s, with nighttime lows in the 
low to mid 50s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
