<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN ARRESTED IN BICYCLIST'S FATAL SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police arrested a a 26-year-old man Friday in connection with the fatal 
drive-by shooting of a bicyclist in the 200 block of South Cliffrose Street on 
Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Graydon Marc Pfeiffer, 26, of Anaheim was arrested on suspicion of murder, 
Sgt. Craig Hunter said.He is being held at the Anaheim City Jail on $250,000 
bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Police identified the victim as Max Gail Downs, 23, also of Anaheim, who was 
riding his bicycle along Cliffrose about 8:35 p.m. Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbors in the quiet residential neighborhood said Friday they discovered 
the body and the bicycle about 9:30 p.m. the night before. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was on a bike and a guy drove by and shot at him," said Hunter, of the 
Police Department's gang detail. But Hunter said there was no evidence that the 
shooting was gang-related or that Pfeiffer was affiliated with any gang. 
</P>
<P>
 Early reports that a dog also had been shot to death proved untrue. 
</P>
