<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN DISCOVERS BODY OF CO-WORKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was found dead in his living room Friday morning by a co-worker 
concerned about his failure to report to his job, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Homicide investigators are looking into the death, said Santa Ana Police Sgt. 
Bob Helton, but it's not certain that foul play was involved.The cause of death 
has not been determined. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have not released the man's name, because relatives have not yet been 
notified. 
</P>
<P>
 The man lived at a large apartment complex in the 2400 block of North Tustin 
Avenue, Helton said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange County coroner's office has scheduled an autopsy today.. 
</P>
<P>
 Helton would not say whether there were signs of trauma to the body. 
</P>
<P>
 He said the co-worker found the door to the upstairs apartment open when he 
went to check on the man at 8 a.m. Friday. 
</P>
