<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL / STATE CHAMPIONSHIP; BAKERSFIELD EAST WINS DIVISION II 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eli Anderson scored a game-high 19 points to lead Bakersfield East High to a 
68-59 victory over Roseville Oakmont in the State Division II boys' 
championship game Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Before 6,640 at the Oakland Coliseum Arena, East (29-4) broke open a close 
game in the second quarter by outscoring Oakmont, 19-11. 
</P>
<P>
 Anthony Flood and Whitney Brake led Oakmont (31-4) with 14 and 12 points, 
respectively. 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego Lincoln Prep 63, San Anselmo Sir Francis Drake 50 -- Mark Sanford, a 
6-foot-8 senior center, scored a game-high 18 points to lead Lincoln (25-7) to 
the Division IV championship at the Oakland Coliseum Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Drake was overpowered from the start as Lincoln took a 24-10 halftime lead. 
Lincoln led by as many as 20 points and Drake never got closer than seven in 
the second half. 
</P>
