<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; BURTON WINDS UP 33RD IN NCAA THREE-METER SPRINGBOARD DIVING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dawn Burton of Cal State Northridge finished 33rd out of 35 entrants in the 
women's three-meter springboard event Friday in the NCAA Division I swimming 
and diving championships at the Indiana University Natatorium in Indianapolis. 
</P>
<P>
 Burton, a freshman, totaled 384.15 points in the preliminaries, but only the 
top eight competitors advanced to the final, which was won by Robin Carter of 
Texas. 
</P>
<P>
 Carter had 522.10 points in the finals after finishing fifth in the 
preliminaries. BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Azusa Pacific 11, The Master's 0 -- Three Mustang pitchers issued 11 walks and 
hit six batters to make it easy for the Cougars. Matt Davis (4-1) took the loss 
for Master's (6-15, 3-6 in the Golden State Athletic Conference). MEN'S 
VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Pierce d. Orange Coast, 15-6, 14-16, 15-7, 15-7 -- Gabe Higa had 28 kills and 
Dan Nash had 79 assists in a Western State Conference match for Pierce (9-0, 
8-0). SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 7-5, Cal Lutheran 1-4 -- Xochitl Castillo had a 
pinch-hit, three-run double in a four-run seventh in the second game, but the 
Regals were swept in a nonconference doubleheader. 
</P>
