EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; MAN GETS YEAR IN 5TH DRUNK-DRIVING CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Van Nuys man convicted of drunk driving for the fifth time in nine years was 
sentenced to a year in jail Thursday, according to the Los Angeles city 
attorney's office. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose de Carmen Flores, 33, was also placed on three years probation after 
pleading guilty to driving drunk with prior convictions and driving on a 
suspended license, according to Deputy City Atty.Debra Siedorf, who handled the 
case. 
</P>
<P>
 Flores was arrested by Los Angeles police in Van Nuys about 2 a.m. Feb. 13 
after they found him in his car, which was parked with the motor running in an 
eastbound traffic lane of Sherman Way near Van Nuys Boulevard. His 
blood-alcohol level was .13. The legal limit is .08. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
