<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: CALABASAS; WATER DISTRICT BOARD APPOINTS COLBAUGH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An interim general manager has been appointed by the Las Virgenes Municipal 
Water District Board. 
</P>
<P>
 James E. Colbaugh, 47, former head of the planning and engineering department, 
was named to the post March 3 after the board decided not to renew the contract 
of former General Manager Charles McClain.The board is seeking a new general 
manager.  
</P>
<P>
 "The board feels it is setting a new course for the district and believes a 
different leadership style will benefit Las Virgenes," spokeswoman Bobbe Wymer 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Colbaugh was not available for comment Friday.  
</P>
<P>
 A 17-year employee of the district, Colbaugh has also served as manager of 
water reclamation facilities and director of water and sanitation operations. A 
registered civil engineer, Colbaugh received a master's degree in environmental 
engineering from Loyola Marymount University and a bachelor's degree in civil 
engineering from Pennsylvania State University. He is an adjunct professor at 
College of the Canyons in Valencia, where he teaches classes in water treatment 
and operations. 
</P>
<P>
 Colbaugh has helped the Conejo Future Foundation develop its water plan and 
serves as the chairman of the national Water Reuse Committee of the Water 
Environment Federation. 
</P>
<P>
 Colbaugh lives in Westlake Village with his wife, Andrea. KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</TEXT>
